{"cursor":"57704","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\nThe 'Vulgate' is a late 4th-century Latin translation of the Bible. It was\nlargely the work of St. Jerome, who was commissioned by Pope Damasus I in 382 to\nmake a revision of the old Latin translations. By the 13th century this revision\nhad come to be called the versio vulgata, that is, the \"commonly used\ntranslation\", [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?-\ndoc=Perseus:text:1999.04.0059:entry=vulgo2 On the etymology of the noun\n(originally an adjective) vulgata] and ultimately it became the definitive\nand officially promulgated Latin version of the Bible in the Roman Catholic\nChurch. Its widespread adoption led to the eclipse of earlier Latin\ntranslations, which are collectively referred to as the Vetus Latina.\n","linknr":-1,"url":"Vulgate","recorded":1362479212,"links":0,"instances":["book_of_daniel"],"pdf":[],"categories":["5th-century books","Early versions of the Bible","Latin language","History of Roman Catholicism","5th-century Christian texts","Works by Jerome","Christian terms","Christian biblical canon"],"headings":["Authorship","Relation with the Old Latin Bible","Influence on Western culture","Texts","See also","References","Further reading","External links"],"image":[],"tags":[["susanna","book_of_daniel"]],"members":["susanna"],"related":["Bible_translations_into_Latin","St_Jerome","Pope_Damasus_I","Vetus_Latina","Roman_Catholic_Church","Vetus_Latina","Book_of_Daniel","The_Prayer_of_Azariah_and_Song_of_the_Three_Holy_Children","Susanna_(Book_of_Daniel)","Bel_and_the_Dragon","Aramaic","Book_of_Tobit","Book_of_Judith","Vetus_Latina","New_Testament_manuscript","Four_Gospels","Book_of_Baruch","Letter_of_Jeremiah","1_Esdras","Acts_of_the_Apostles","Book_of_Revelation","Epistle_to_the_Laodiceans","Prayer_of_Manasses","2_Esdras","Book_of_Wisdom","Ecclesiasticus","1_Maccabees","2_Maccabees","Domenico_Ghirlandaio","Damasus_I","Four_Gospels","Psalter","New_Testament","Bet